SIGNSavvy Project

AWS link for the recordings of the group members for the different gestures: http://34.219.189.217/files/27/ 
alternative drive link of the gesture recordings: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1RGQXTIQuc9RkXUhi3_0V-jhwJb48LB2T/view?usp=sharing

import code into Android Studio

Run the app

On the main screen.
Enter last Name , ASU id which will be used for generating the file name

In the dropdown all the gestures are mentioned, click the gesture to be taken to the practice page.

On the screen 2, the practice video comes up with the PRACTICE button

On screen 3, you can start and stop recording and also have the option to upload.
It will be uploaded to the ubuntu server.


